Privacy Policy
This Privacy policy defines the procedure for processing of personal data and measures to ensure security of personal data, undertaken by «WordsPictures» Ltd. (here in after – «we», «us», «our» etc…).
1.1. Our important mission and condition of carrying out of our activities is to ensure the rights and freedoms when processing their personal data, including privacy protection for the rights to privacy, personal and family life private.
1.2. This Privacy policy with respect to processing of personal data (here in after – Policy) applies to all information, which we can receive about Users of our App HobbEdu (here in after – «App»), when You register or buy/subscribe to our products and services.
1.3. Read this Policy carefully before using our App.
Your access to and use of the App is conditional on your acceptance of and adherence to this Policy. This Policy applies to all Users and others who access or use the App.
You represent and warrant that you are an adult individual to enter into a contract (or, if not, you have obtained permission from your parent or guardian to use the App and have obtained the consent of your parent or guardian to accept the terms of this Policy on your behalf).
The use of App means the unconditional consent of the User with this Policy and the conditions for processing his personal information specified therein; in case of disagreement with these conditions, the User must refrain from use of the App.
2. What information we collect and use
2.1. When using our App, we will collect the following User information:
2.1.1. Personal information that the User provides about himself or herself when registering (creating an account) or when buying/subscribing to our products and services:
– name and the User’s nickname;
– email address;
– studied languages and languages currently being studied;
– country where the User lives;
– credit or debit card information, your bank account number and sort code information, or other banking information related to payment when using the App.
2.1.2. Data that is automatically generated during the using of the App:
– access log;
– device information;
– IP-address;
– information about the cookie;
– statistical data;
– your account information (payment dates due and received, subscription services you use, or any other information associated with your account).
2.3. Personal data is used in the analysis of the management and use of our App, as well as for statistics based on the provided personal information in a format that cannot be used to identify individual Users and can use this data without any restrictions.
3. How we use the personal data of Users
3.1. All personal data that we collect from you will be used in accordance with applicable laws on the protection of personal data and this Privacy Policy. We will process your personal data as follows:
– to provide access to the use of the App and to authenticate the identity of the Users;
– to provide various information free of charge in emails from us;
– to establish User feedback, including sending notifications, requests regarding the use of the App, the provision of services, processing requests, applications, complaints, received from the User, etc.;
– to notify Users about changes in the rules of the use of the App, etc.;
– to improve our App and develop new services for Users;
– marketing analytics;
– to carry out advertising activities with the consent of the User.
3.2. Users can request the correction, addition or deletion of personal information based on the Law on Protection of Personal Data, by writing to us at the email address info@wordspicturesltd.com.
3.3. We collect and store only that personal information that is necessary for the provision of services when you use our App or the execution of agreements and contracts with the User, except for cases when the legislation provides for the mandatory storage of personal information for a period specified by law.
3.4. A condition for the termination of the processing of personal data may be the achievement of the purposes of processing personal data, the expiration of the User’s consent or withdrawal of consent by the User, as well as the identification of illegal processing of personal data.
4. Transfer of personal data to third parties
4.1. The User’s personal data will never, under any circumstances be transferred to third parties, except in cases related to the implementation of current legislation or if the User has given us consent to transfer data to a third party to fulfill obligations under the contract.
4.2. All information that is collected by third-party services, including payment systems, communication facilities and other service providers, is stored and processed by the specified persons (Operators) in accordance with their User Agreement and Privacy Policy. The subject of personal data and/or the User is obliged to independently refer to these documents in a timely manner. We are not responsible for the actions of third parties, including the service providers specified in this clause.
4.3. We have the right to transfer the User’s personal information to third parties in the following cases:
– The User has consented to such actions;
– the transfer is necessary for the User to use a certain service or to fulfill a certain agreement or contract with the User;
– the transfer is provided for by Russian or other applicable law within the framework of the procedure established by law;
– in the event of the sale of the App, all obligations to comply with the terms of this Policy in relation to the personal information received by the purchaser are transferred.
4.4. We are not responsible for the acquisition of personal data by third parties under the following circumstances:
– when the User discloses personal information to another User using the functions of the App or in any other way;
– when the User can be identified by chance using activity data and information entered by another User;
– when an individual User receives information that can be used to identify the User (ID, password, etc.).
5. Legal grounds for processing personal data and conditions for processing personal data
5.1. The legal grounds for the processing, collection, storage, transfer of your personal data by us are:
– contracts concluded between us and the User for the use of our App when you register in it and/or buy/subscribe to our services products;
– applicable privacy laws, including federal law and regulations in the field of personal data protection of the Russian Federation;
GDPR and related internal laws and regulations in the field of personal data protection of Users residing in EU countries;
Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) when our App is used in the United States;
in accordance with the APEC International Privacy Rule (CBPR) and the system of recognition of privacy requirements for personal data processors, for Users residing in the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) countries and other laws of the countries in which our App is used;
– Users’ consent to the processing of their personal data, personal data of the User’s children to the processing of personal data permitted for distribution.
5.2. We process the User’s personal data only if it is filled in and / or sent by the User independently through special forms located in the App or sent to us via email. By filling out the appropriate forms and/or sending his personal data to us, the User agrees with this Policy.
5.3. We process anonymized data about the User if it is allowed in the settings of the User’s browser (the storage of cookies and the use of JavaScript technology are enabled).
5.4. The user independently decides on the provision of his personal data and the data of his child and gives consent freely, of his own free will and in his interest.
5.5. The processing of the User’s personal data is carried out without any time limit in any legal way, including in personal data information systems using automation tools or without using such tools. The processing of personal data of Users is carried out in accordance with the laws specified in clause 5.1. of this Policy.
5.6. We take the necessary organizational and technical measures to protect the User’s personal information from unauthorized or accidental access, destruction, modification, blocking, copying, distribution, as well as from other illegal actions of third parties.
5.7. We together with the User, take all necessary measures to prevent losses or other negative consequences caused by the loss or disclosure of the User’s personal data.
6. Children and personal data
6.1. We understand the importance of protecting the personal data of children, by which we mean persons under the age of 16 or a similar age as established by the laws of your country.
6.2. Parents should read this section carefully before creating a child account on our App. If parents agree with this procedure, they can use our App for their children.
6.3. In accordance with this Policy, we may use your child’s information to deliver important messages and send information, information about products and services, notifications, provide services, provide content and improve the quality of our products, content and services. We may also use your child’s information for internal purposes such as auditing, data analysis and research.
6.4. We have the right to use, transfer and disclose information that does not belong to personal data (that is, information that does not allow us to directly associate it with the identity of your child) for any purpose. For example, we have the right to combine and use information about the activity of Users in our App, which will allow us to provide our Users with more useful information and understand which sections of our App and components of products and services are of greatest interest to them or, on the contrary, difficulties. The combined data is not considered personal information.
6.5. Our App does not display personalized advertisements. Targeted ads will not be shown to your child. However, your child may still see inappropriate (i.e.contextual) ads in our App. In addition, a tracking request from Apps will be banned, and this ban cannot be lifted.
6.6. All sections and clauses of this Policy also apply to your children.
7. Links to other sites
7.1. Our App may contain links to other sites, apps that are not operated by us. If you click on a link of a third party, you will be redirected to that third party’s site. We strongly recommend that you read the Privacy Policy of each site you visit. We do not control and are not responsible for the content, privacy policies or practices of any sites, apps or services of third party.
8. Data storage
8.1. We will only keep your personal data for as long as is necessary to fulfill the purposes for which we collected it, including to meet any legal, accounting or reporting requirements.
8.2. To determine the appropriate storage period for personal data, we take into account the volume, nature and sensitivity of personal data, the potential risk of harm as a result of unauthorized use or disclosure of your personal data, the purposes for which we process your personal data and whether we can achieve these goals in other ways as well as applicable legal requirements.
8.3. We are required by law to retain basic information about our customers (including contact, identification, financial and transaction data) for four years after they cease to be customers for tax purposes.
In some cases, you can ask us to delete your data.
9. Intellectual property rights
9.1. The app you are using is for your personal, non-commercial use only and is for informational, educational and entertainment purposes only.
9.2. All contents of the App are our property, protected by copyright, and all trademarks and other intellectual property rights belong to «Words Pictures» Ltd. You may own the physical media on which elements of the App are delivered to you, but we retain full ownership of the content in the App. We do not transfer ownership of any content to you.
10. Software license
10.1. If the App is configured to allow the use of software, content, virtual items, or other material owned or licensed by us, we grant you a limited, non-exclusive, non-sublicense right to access and use such software, content, virtual items or other materials for your personal, non-commercial use only.
10.2. You may not circumvent or disable any content protection or digital rights management technology used with any App;
decompile, reverse engineer, disassemble or otherwise reduce any Service to a readable form;
remove identity, copyright, or other proprietary notices; and access or use any Service in an illegal or unauthorized manner or in a manner that involves association with our products, services or brands.
11. Changes to this Policy
11.1. We reserve the right to make changes to this Policy on a regular basis. The user is obliged to regularly check and confirm the applicable provisions in accordance with his responsibilities.
11.2 In the event of a conflict between Applicable Privacy Laws and any provision of this Policy, this provision shall be deemed to be superseded by a provision of the same meaning that reflects the original intent, to the maximum extent permitted by law. In this case, the remaining provisions of this Policy continue to apply unchanged.
